      "sc:description": "snpFreq significant SNPs in case-control data. \n\nThis tool performs a basic analysis of bi-allelic SNPs in case-control data, using the R statistical environment and Fisher''s exact test to identify SNPs with a significant difference in the allele frequencies between the two groups.  R''s \"qvalue\" package is used to correct for multiple testing.",
      "sc:featureList": {
        "@id": "edam:operation_0484"
      },
      "sc:name": "snpfreq",
      "sc:softwareVersion": "1.0.1",
      "sc:url": "https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-devteam/tree/main/tool_collections/hgv/snpfreq"
    },
